value.title: Trump Says Kamala Harris 'Won't Be First Woman President,' Rallygoers Demand Ivanka
value.excerpt: Trump said Kamala Harris will "take over" for Biden three weeks into his term if he wins before declaring, "she will not be the first woman president" Tuesday at a Lansing, Michigan campaign event.

value.title: Trump promised massive middle-class tax cuts in 2016. He delivered cuts, not as much on the middle class part
value.excerpt: The GOP tax bill in 2017 gave households an average $1,600 cut but the richest Americans, especially those making over $300,000, got the most relief.

value.title: Fact check: Trump falsely claims Pennsylvanians 'can't go to church'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump keeps falsely declaring that various states run by Democratic governors are "closed" or "shut down."

value.title: Biden makes plea to ‘unite and heal’ the country during stop in Georgia
value.excerpt: Joe Biden, playing offense in a long time red state turned crucial battleground this year, made a closing campaign pitch on Tuesday for national unity to rise above what he called the division President Trump’s sown during his four years in the White House.

value.title: Trump already chose Barrett successor on appeals court, confirmation possible regardless of election outcome
value.excerpt: With Justice Amy Coney Barrett now on the Supreme Court, a new vacancy has opened on the 7th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals where she previously sat, and President Trump has already named the person he plans to have replace her on that bench.

value.title: Pence's office says he did not attend swearing-in due to CDC guidelines
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence did not attend Monday night's White House swearing-in ceremony for Supreme Court Justice Amy Coney Barrett because he was adhering to US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention guidelines to prevent the spread of the coronavirus, an administration official told CNN.

value.title: Twitter labels Trump post about mail ballots as ‘disputed’ and ‘misleading’

value.title: Judge rejects DOJ's attempt to defend Trump in E. Jean Carroll rape defamation lawsuit
value.excerpt: A federal judge on Tuesday denied the Justice Department's effort to intervene in a defamation lawsuit brought against President Donald Trump by a longtime magazine columnist who has alleged he raped her, paving the way for the case to proceed.

value.title: Coal baron Murray, a Trump ally who fought environmental regulation, dead at 80
value.excerpt: U.S. coal baron Robert Murray, an ally of President Donald Trump and a leading industry voice who called global warming a hoax, died on Sunday at age 80, U.S. media reported.

value.title: Trump remakes Supreme Court as Senate confirms Amy Coney Barrett
value.excerpt: The Republican-led U.S. Senate handed President Donald Trump a major pre-election political victory on Monday by confirming his Supreme Court nominee Amy Coney Barrett as he delivered a dramatic conservative overhaul of the nation's top judicial body.

value.title: Biden raises idea of rotating Supreme Court justices: 'There is some literature among constitutional scholars'
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Joe Biden indicated on Monday that he might be open to shifting Supreme Court justices to lower courts if elected president, noting that he hadn't made any "judgement" yet on the issue.

value.title: Ivanka Trump, Jared Kushner threaten to sue over billboard
value.excerpt: Ivanka Trump and Jared Kushner are threatening to sue The Lincoln Project over billboards the organization erected in New York City's Times Square. CNN's Brianna Keilar and Alexandra Field report.

value.title: Kayleigh McEnany once praised Biden as a 'man of the people' who resonates with "middle class" over 'tycoon' Trump
value.excerpt: Prior to becoming a prominent backer of Donald Trump, Kayleigh McEnany praised then-Vice President Joe Biden as "funny and likable" and a "man of the people" who resonates with "middle class voters."

value.title: Trump and Pence defy pandemic for political gain
value.excerpt: President Trump and Vice President Pence are holding events in battleground states, defiant about the pandemic, a White House outbreak and a climbing national case count.

value.title: Pence skips public health recommended self-quarantine but does change plans after staff outbreak
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence, despite flouting public health guidelines by still campaigning after being exposed to people testing positive with coronavirus, is taking some precautions on the road.

value.title: Pence campaigns with 'medically informed' approach to events after staffers test positive for COVID-19
value.excerpt: Vice President Pence has returned to the campaign trail after key staffers tested positive for the novel coronavirus, however his team is taking a “thoughtful” and “medically-informed” approach to his travel this week in the final stretch until Election Day.
